	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Western Cape police are investigating the shooting of a 40-year-old man on Saturday afternoon in Bonteheuwel. "At approximately 15:30 on August 25, a man was shot and injured at the corner of Jakkals Vlei and Jakes Gerwel drive [in] Bonteheuwel, Bishop Lavis," Captain FC Van Wyk told News 24. Police confirmed that a case of attempted murder is being investigated. Further details were not immediately available. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  